{#
  landing.html.j2 — grouped landing page for the multi-user web-terminal stack.

  Rendered by render_web_terminals() (Task 1.4) and served as a plain static file by
  nginx — there is no app route behind this page, so it must stay self-contained
  (inline CSS, no external assets, no build step).

  Template variables (contract with the caller):

    facility_name: str, optional
      Shown in the page header. Falls back to "OSPREY" when empty/undefined.

    groups: list[dict], required
      Ordered list of groups to render:
        {
          "label": str,            # group heading, e.g. "Terminals" or "Dashboards"
          "items": list[dict],     # [{"label": str, "url": str, "sublabel"?: str}, ...]
        }
      ONE shared loop renders every group in this list — the `users` group is not
      special-cased beyond how its data arrives:
        - The `users` group is auto-populated by the caller from facility-config
          `users[]`: one item per user, `{label: <username>, url: <that user's
          terminal origin>}`, plus an OPTIONAL `sublabel` holding that user's
          persona name when one is in effect (a bare-string roster with no persona
          omits the key entirely).
        - All other groups are operator-supplied `{label, url}` lists straight out of
          facility-config.
      `sublabel` is optional on every item: when present it renders as a secondary
      persona badge on the card; when absent the card renders exactly as a plain
      `{label, url}` card (bracket-subscripting a missing key yields Jinja
      `Undefined`, which is falsy — see the `{% if item["sublabel"] %}` guard).
      A group whose `items` list is empty renders nothing — no heading, no empty
      section. This is the ONLY suppression rule, and it is generic to every group:
      it's what makes the 0-user case disappear cleanly (an empty/omitted `users`
      group) while any other configured group still renders normally.

  Escaping: this template is rendered with a Jinja2 Environment that has autoescape
  ON (HTML). `label`/`url` are still explicitly piped through `|e` wherever they're
  interpolated, as defense-in-depth per the framework's escapeHtml convention —
  `url` in particular is treated as untrusted operator input, not just `label`.

  URL scheme: HTML-escaping alone does not neutralize a `url` like
  `"javascript:...\"` — it would still render as a live, clickable link that
  executes script on click. `url` is checked against an http(s)/site-relative
  allowlist before it is ever used in an `href` (same check gates the display
  text); a `url` with any other scheme renders its card inert (no `<a>`, no
  navigation) instead of being dropped, so a misconfigured group is still visible.
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{{ (facility_name|default("", true))|e or "OSPREY" }} Web Terminals</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      color-scheme: dark;
      --bg-primary: #0a0f1a;
      --bg-panel: #0e1525;
      --bg-elevated: #1a2332;
      --text-primary: #f1f5f9;
      --text-secondary: #8b9ab5;
      --text-muted: #64748b;
      --color-accent: #4fd1c5;
      --border-default: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.16);
      --border-accent: rgba(79, 209, 197, 0.35);
      --shadow-card: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35);
    }
    @media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
      :root {
        color-scheme: light;
        --bg-primary: #f7f9fc;
        --bg-panel: #ffffff;
        --bg-elevated: #eef2f7;
        --text-primary: #0c1322;
        --text-secondary: #45526b;
        --text-muted: #64748b;
        --color-accent: #0a8f8c;
        --border-default: #d9dfe8;
        --border-accent: rgba(10, 143, 140, 0.35);
        --shadow-card: 0 4px 16px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.08);
      }
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      background: var(--bg-primary);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .landing-header {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 960px;
      padding: 2.5rem 1.5rem 1rem;
    }
    .landing-title {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 400;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .landing-logo {
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 1.35rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--color-accent);
    }
    .landing-subtitle {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .landing-main {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 960px;
      flex: 1;
      padding: 0.5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }
    .landing-empty {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .landing-group {
      margin-top: 2rem;
    }
    .landing-group-label {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }
    .landing-cards {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .landing-card {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.3rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
      background: var(--bg-panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-default);
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-card);
      text-decoration: none;
      color: inherit;
      transition: border-color 120ms ease, transform 120ms ease, background 120ms ease;
      min-width: 0;
    }
    .landing-card:hover,
    .landing-card:focus-visible {
      border-color: var(--border-accent);
      background: var(--bg-elevated);
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }
    .landing-card:focus-visible {
      outline: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
      outline-offset: 2px;
    }
    .landing-card-inert {
      cursor: not-allowed;
      opacity: 0.6;
      border-style: dashed;
    }
    .landing-card-inert:hover {
      border-color: var(--border-default);
      background: var(--bg-panel);
      transform: none;
    }
    .landing-card-label {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .landing-card-sublabel {
      align-self: flex-start;
      max-width: 100%;
      margin: 0.05rem 0 0.1rem;
      padding: 0.12rem 0.55rem;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-accent);
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--color-accent);
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .landing-card-url {
      font-family: ui-monospace, "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      overflow: hidden;
      text-overflow: ellipsis;
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    .landing-footer {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 960px;
      padding: 1rem 1.5rem 2rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="landing-header">
    <h1 class="landing-title">
      <span class="landing-logo">OSPREY</span>
      <span class="landing-subtitle">{{ (facility_name|default("", true))|e or "Web Terminals" }}</span>
    </h1>
  </header>

  <main class="landing-main">
    {#- Generic emptiness check: true only when every group's items list is empty. #}
    {% set ns = namespace(any_visible=false) %}
    {% for group in groups|default([]) %}
      {% if group["items"] %}{% set ns.any_visible = true %}{% endif %}
    {% endfor %}

    {% if not ns.any_visible %}
      <p class="landing-empty">No terminals or links are configured yet.</p>
    {% endif %}

    {% for group in groups|default([]) %}
      {% if group["items"] %}
      <section class="landing-group">
        <h2 class="landing-group-label">{{ group["label"]|e }}</h2>
        <div class="landing-cards">
          {% for item in group["items"] %}
          {#- |e alone escapes markup but not the URL *scheme* — a raw "javascript:"/
             "data:"/"vbscript:" url would still render as a live, clickable
             script-execution link. Allowlist by inclusion of known-safe schemes
             (http, https, site-relative) rather than by excluding bad ones, and
             reuse the SAME normalized value for both the href and the display text.
             A leading "//" is EXCLUDED from the site-relative branch: browsers
             resolve "//host/path" as a scheme-relative off-origin URL (same as
             "https://host/path"), so "//evil.com/x" is a bypass, not a relative
             path, and must be treated as unsafe like javascript:/data:. #}
          {% set raw_url = item["url"] if item["url"] is string else "" %}
          {% set is_relative = raw_url.startswith("/") and not raw_url.startswith("//") %}
          {% set is_http = raw_url.startswith("http://") or raw_url.startswith("https://") %}
          {% set safe_url = raw_url if (is_http or is_relative) else "" %}
          {% if safe_url %}
          <a class="landing-card" href="{{ safe_url|e }}">
            <span class="landing-card-label">{{ item["label"]|e }}</span>
            {%- if item["sublabel"] %}
            <span class="landing-card-sublabel">{{ item["sublabel"]|e }}</span>
            {%- endif %}
            <span class="landing-card-url">{{ safe_url|e }}</span>
          </a>
          {% else %}
          <div class="landing-card landing-card-inert" title="Unsupported link scheme">
            <span class="landing-card-label">{{ item["label"]|e }}</span>
            {%- if item["sublabel"] %}
            <span class="landing-card-sublabel">{{ item["sublabel"]|e }}</span>
            {%- endif %}
            <span class="landing-card-url">unsupported link</span>
          </div>
          {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </section>
      {% endif %}
    {% endfor %}
  </main>

  <footer class="landing-footer">
    OSPREY multi-user web terminal stack
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
